column1: event,"Ok so I thought I had updated this thing on tuesday. But its not here... Oh well. So here it is. On wednesday of last week I left for LSU. That trip was to make my schedule and take some tests. I was able too bump myself up to Math 1550 because of my test scores and Also I don't have to do first semester of english. I am taking 16 hours, 5 classes. Math 1550, Geology 1001, Petroleum Engineering 1010, Chemistry 1201, and English 1002. This orientation was fun, but its not the ""real"" orientation where we just have fun. After I finished with that, I started on my way to Pensacola. Pensacola was lots of fun. The first night I got there, everyone was at dinner so I just sat around in the lobby of the hotel and read my book for about 30 minutes. After that it was the factoid game. I really didn't play. Next up was sleep time. The next morning woke up early for the meet. Warm-up was a killer for me, and then it was time for the 200 free. I added 10 seconds to that. Then time for the killer event, 200 fly... Added somewhere around 24 seconds to that one. :) Went to the hotel and watched tv, then went to dinner. After dinner it was fishing time. We left at 10:30 that night and finally started fishing around 11:15. Didn't get back to the hotel until 3:30. We started off the first hour not catching anything, then decided to move closer in to the shore. Thats when we started catching stuff. I caught 5 or 6 fish, i lost count.. I had the MONSTER catch of the night, you will never believe the size of this fish!! Finall got to bed around 4 am just in time for 2 hours of sleep before it was time to swim the 800. Went a best time! After the meet went to the beach and built a sand turtle and a sand crab. There were lots and lots of jelly fish around. Ordered pizza and watched tv. Next morning it was raining too hard to go to the beach. Instead we went to a store and then started home. Get home around 10:00 and clean up then go to sleepo. Tuesday started up my working again. Worked 7-11 like always and then at 12-5. wednesday I worked 7-11 and then 3-930. That was fun because no one came to the pool from 3-5 and then swim lessons. Today i work 7-11 and then 12-5. I can actually do something tonight so who knows.
Thats about all for now. Have fun

event,"Ok, so far i have seen Troy, Shrek 2, Man on Fire, Harry Potter and the prisoner of azkabaan, Day After Tommorow, and a few others that I dont remember the names too. Only about 44 more movies to see this summer! So far they have all been good. Other than those movies, most of my life has been working. Wednesday I go to LSU for orientation then from there its off to pensacola. That will be fun since I haven't actually been to a real practice for about 2 months. Hope I live. Thats about all I can think of right now. Buh Bye"
